      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Unfortunately, in this case we fail spectacularly.\n",
        "The predictions decay to a constant\n",
        "pretty quickly after a few steps.\n",
        "Why did the algorithm perform so much worse\n",
        "when predicting further into the future?\n",
        "Ultimately, this is down to the fact\n",
        "that errors build up.\n",
        "Let's say that after step 1 we have some error $\\epsilon_1 = \\bar\\epsilon$.\n",
        "Now the *input* for step 2 is perturbed by $\\epsilon_1$,\n",
        "hence we suffer some error in the order of\n",
        "$\\epsilon_2 = \\bar\\epsilon + c \\epsilon_1$\n",
        "for some constant $c$, and so on.\n",
        "The predictions can diverge rapidly\n",
        "from the true observations.\n",
        "You may already be familiar\n",
        "with this common phenomenon.\n",
        "For instance, weather forecasts for the next 24 hours\n",
        "tend to be pretty accurate but beyond that,\n",
        "accuracy declines rapidly.\n",
        "We will discuss methods for improving this\n",
        "throughout this chapter and beyond.\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's take a closer look at the difficulties in $k$-step-ahead predictions by computing predictions on the entire sequence for $k = 1, 4, 16, 64$.\n",
        "\n",
        "### K step ahead predictions"
      ],
      "id": "fb898d97"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| eval: true\n",
        "\n",
        "def k_step_pred(model, data, k):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Vectorized k-step-ahead prediction following D2L semantics.\n",
        "    Returns a list of tensors, where the i-th element is the (i+1)-step prediction.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    T = data.T\n",
        "    tau = data.tau\n",
        "    x = data.x\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Step 1: initial tau feature rows (true data)\n",
        "    features = []\n",
        "    for i in range(tau):\n",
        "        # shape: [T - tau - k + 1]\n",
        "        features.append(x[i : i + T - tau - k + 1])\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Step 2: generate k future steps\n",
        "    for i in range(k):\n",
        "        # Stack the last tau rows to form the feature matrix\n",
        "        window = torch.stack(features[i : i + tau], dim=1)  # shape: [N, tau]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Predict next step\n",
        "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "            preds = model(window).reshape(-1)  # shape: [N]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Append predictions as the next row\n",
        "        features.append(preds)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Step 3: return only the predicted rows (skip the initial tau)\n",
        "    return features[tau:]"
      ],
      "id": "f58b4e22",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| eval: true\n",
        "steps = (1, 4, 16, 64)\n",
        "pred_rows = k_step_pred(model, data, steps[-1])"
      ],
      "id": "4bfe37dc",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
