        "## Converting Raw Text into Sequence Data\n",
        "\n",
        "Throughout the class, we will often work with text data\n",
        "represented as sequences\n",
        "of words, characters, or word pieces.\n",
        "To get going, we will need some basic\n",
        "tools for converting raw text\n",
        "into sequences of the appropriate form.\n",
        "Typical preprocessing pipelines\n",
        "execute the following steps:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Load text as strings into memory.\n",
        "2. Split the strings into tokens (e.g., words or characters).\n",
        "3. Build a vocabulary dictionary to associate each vocabulary element with a numerical index.\n",
        "4. Convert the text into sequences of numerical indices."
      ],
      "id": "011369e5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| eval: true\n",
        "\n",
        "import collections\n",
        "import os\n",
        "import re\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "import random\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "import requests"
      ],
      "id": "1aa20ec2",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Reading the Dataset\n",
        "\n",
        "Here, we will work with H. G. Wells'\n",
        "[The Time Machine](http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/35),\n",
        "a book containing just over 30,000 words.\n",
        "While real applications will typically\n",
        "involve significantly larger datasets,\n",
        "this is sufficient to demonstrate\n",
        "the preprocessing pipeline.\n",
        "Let's download the dataset programmatically. This is a simple `.txt` file download. We can also utilize `BeautifulSoup` to scrape the text from the website, but that is not necessary here."
      ],
      "id": "0d566b39"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| eval: true\n",
        "#| \n",
        "\n",
        "class TimeMachine:\n",
        "    URL = \"https://d2l-data.s3-accelerate.amazonaws.com/timemachine.txt\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __init__(self, root=\"data\"):\n",
        "        self.root = root\n",
        "        os.makedirs(root, exist_ok=True)\n",
        "        self.path = os.path.join(root, \"timemachine.txt\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        self.raw_text = self._download()\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Cached values (initially None)\n",
        "        self.cleaned_text = None\n",
        "        self.tokens = None\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _download(self):\n",
        "        if not os.path.exists(self.path):\n",
        "            print(\"Downloading Time Machine dataset...\")\n",
        "            r = requests.get(self.URL)\n",
        "            with open(self.path, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n",
        "                f.write(r.text)\n",
        "        with open(self.path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n",
        "            return f.read()\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _preprocess(self, text):\n",
        "        text = text.lower()\n",
        "        text = re.sub(r'[^a-z]+', ' ', text)\n",
        "        text = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip()\n",
        "        return text\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _tokenize(self, text):\n",
        "        return list(text)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # NEW: ensures cleaned_text and tokens exist\n",
        "    def prepare(self):\n",
        "        if self.cleaned_text is None:\n",
        "            self.cleaned_text = self._preprocess(self.raw_text)\n",
        "        if self.tokens is None:\n",
        "            self.tokens = self._tokenize(self.cleaned_text)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def build(self, raw_text=None, vocab=None):\n",
        "        raw_text = raw_text or self.raw_text\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Cache cleaned text + tokens\n",
        "        self.cleaned_text = self._preprocess(raw_text)\n",
        "        self.tokens = self._tokenize(self.cleaned_text)\n",
        "\n",
        "        if vocab is None:\n",
        "            vocab = Vocab(self.tokens)\n",
        "\n",
        "        corpus = [vocab[token] for token in self.tokens]\n",
        "        return corpus, vocab\n",
        "\n",
        "data = TimeMachine()\n",
        "data.prepare()\n",
        "print(data.raw_text[:60])"
      ],
